FAQs
What are the benefits of studying in the USA?

Studying in the USA offers access to top-ranked universities, diverse academic programs, cultural diversity, and innovative research opportunities.

How can Qadri-International help with my application process?

Qadri-International provides personalized guidance, university selection assistance, comprehensive application support, and visa and immigration guidance.

Are there work opportunities for international students in the USA?

Yes, international students can work part-time while studying and participate in the Optional Practical Training (OPT) program after graduation.

What are the living costs for students in the USA?

Living costs vary depending on the city and lifestyle, but students can manage expenses through part-time work and scholarships.

How do I choose the right university in the USA?

Qadri-International helps you choose the right university by considering your academic profile, career goals, and personal preferences.

